<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FF8AFFC0A7ADFCB5FD05D833" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0755A263FF8AFFC0A7ADFCB5FEF0DF75" blockId="19.[189,310,858,884]" box="[189,310,858,884]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<heading id="5C1D150FFF8AFFC0A7ADFCB5FEF0DF75" bold="true" box="[189,310,858,884]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF8AFFC0A7ADFCB5FEF0DF75" bold="true" box="[189,310,858,884]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF8AFFC0A7ADFC66FD05D833" blockId="19.[189,1400,905,1074]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
This species may be separated from other Caribbean and Central American 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF8AFFC0A353FC66FB76DFA2" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[1091,1200,905,931]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF8AFFC0A353FC66FB76DFA2" box="[1091,1200,905,931]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Charinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by means of the following combination of characters: median eyes and ocular tubercle absent; gonopods cushion-like; cheliceral claw with four teeth; cusps of bifid tooth of basal cheliceral segment with dorsal and ventral projections of equal size; tibia of leg I with 23 articles; tarsus I with 41 articles, first article of leg I tarsus three or four times as long as second article.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
